{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'm really scared. I don't think we're going to make it."},{"time":7000,"text":"Probably by now most of you have seen Al Gore's amazing talk."},{"time":11000,"text":"Shortly after I saw that, we had some friends over for dinner"},{"time":15000,"text":"with the family. The conversation turned to global warming,"},{"time":19000,"text":"and everybody agreed, there's a real problem."},{"time":23000,"text":"We've got a climate crisis."},{"time":25000,"text":"So, we went around the table to talk about what we should do."},{"time":30000,"text":"The conversation came to my 15-year-old daughter, Mary."},{"time":35000,"text":"She said, \"I agree with everything that's been said."},{"time":40000,"text":"I'm scared and I'm angry.\" And then she turned to me and said,"},{"time":45000,"text":"\"Dad, your generation created this problem; you'd better fix it.\" Wow."},{"time":53000,"text":"All the conversation stopped. All the eyes turned to me."},{"time":57000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":62000,"text":"I didn't know what to say. Kleiner's second law is,"},{"time":67000,"text":"\"There is a time when panic is the appropriate response.\""},{"time":71000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":72000,"text":"And we've reached that time. We cannot afford to underestimate"},{"time":78000,"text":"this problem. If we face irreversible and catastrophic consequences,"},{"time":86000,"text":"we must act, and we must act decisively."},{"time":89000,"text":"I've got to tell you, for me, everything changed that evening."}]},{"cues":[{"time":93000,"text":"And so, my partners and I, we set off on this mission to learn more,"},{"time":97000,"text":"to try to do much more. So, we mobilized. We got on airplanes."},{"time":101000,"text":"We went to Brazil. We went to China and to India,"},{"time":104000,"text":"to Bentonville, Arkansas, to Washington, D.C. and to Sacramento."},{"time":109000,"text":"And so, what I'd like to do now is to tell you"},{"time":112000,"text":"about what we've learned in those journeys."},{"time":115000,"text":"Because the more we learned, the more concerned we grew."},{"time":118000,"text":"You know, my partners at Kleiner and I were compulsive networkers,"},{"time":120000,"text":"and so when we see a big problem or an opportunity"},{"time":123000,"text":"like avian flu or personalized medicine,"},{"time":126000,"text":"we just get together the smartest people we know."},{"time":129000,"text":"For this climate crisis, we assembled a network, really,"},{"time":133000,"text":"of superstars, from policy activists to scientists and entrepreneurs"},{"time":138000,"text":"and business leaders. Fifty or so of them."},{"time":140000,"text":"And so, I want to tell you about what we've learned in doing that"},{"time":144000,"text":"and four lessons I've learned in the last year."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"The first lesson is that companies are really powerful,"},{"time":151000,"text":"and that matters a lot. This is a story about"},{"time":154000,"text":"how Wal-Mart went green, and what that means."},{"time":157000,"text":"Two years ago, the CEO, Lee Scott, believed that green is"},{"time":162000,"text":"the next big thing, and so Wal-Mart made going green a top priority."},{"time":168000,"text":"They committed that they're going to take their existing stores"},{"time":170000,"text":"and reduce their energy consumption by 20 percent,"},{"time":173000,"text":"and their new stores by 30 percent, and do all that in seven years."},{"time":179000,"text":"The three biggest uses of energy in a store are heating"},{"time":182000,"text":"and air conditioning, then lighting, and then refrigeration."},{"time":186000,"text":"So, look what they did."},{"time":188000,"text":"They painted the roofs of all their stores white."},{"time":191000,"text":"They put smart skylights through their stores"},{"time":193000,"text":"so they could harvest the daylight and reduce the lighting demands."},{"time":197000,"text":"And, third, they put the refrigerated goods"},{"time":199000,"text":"behind closed doors with LED lighting."},{"time":202000,"text":"I mean, why would you try to refrigerate a whole store?"},{"time":205000,"text":"These are really simple, smart solutions based on existing technology."}]},{"cues":[{"time":210000,"text":"Why does Wal-Mart matter? Well, it's massive."},{"time":213000,"text":"They're the largest private employer in America."},{"time":216000,"text":"They're the largest private user of electricity."},{"time":218000,"text":"They have the second-largest vehicle fleet on the road."},{"time":222000,"text":"And they have one of the world's most amazing supply chains,"},{"time":225000,"text":"60,000 suppliers. If Wal-Mart were a country,"},{"time":229000,"text":"it would be the sixth-largest trading partner with China."},{"time":232000,"text":"And maybe most important, they have a big effect on other companies."}]},{"cues":[{"time":237000,"text":"When Wal-Mart declares it's going to go green and be profitable,"},{"time":242000,"text":"it has a powerful impact on other great institutions."},{"time":245000,"text":"So, let me tell you this:"},{"time":246000,"text":"when Wal-Mart achieves 20 percent energy reductions,"},{"time":249000,"text":"that's going to be a very big deal. But I'm afraid it's not enough."},{"time":255000,"text":"We need Wal-Mart and every other company to do the same."}]},{"cues":[{"time":260000,"text":"The second thing that we learned is that individuals matter,"},{"time":263000,"text":"and they matter enormously."},{"time":266000,"text":"I've got another Wal-Mart story for you, OK?"},{"time":268000,"text":"Wal-Mart has over 125 million U.S. customers."},{"time":271000,"text":"That's a third of the U.S. population."},{"time":275000,"text":"65 million compact fluorescent light bulbs were sold last year."},{"time":280000,"text":"And Wal-Mart has committed they're going to sell"},{"time":283000,"text":"another 100 million light bulbs in the coming year. But it's not easy."},{"time":288000,"text":"Consumers don't really like these light bulbs."},{"time":290000,"text":"The light's kind of funny, they won't dim,"},{"time":292000,"text":"takes a while for them to start up."},{"time":294000,"text":"But the pay-off is really enormous."},{"time":297000,"text":"100 million compact fluorescent light bulbs means"},{"time":300000,"text":"that we'll save 600 million dollars in energy bills,"},{"time":304000,"text":"and 20 million tons of CO2 every year, year in and year out."},{"time":311000,"text":"It does seem really hard to get consumers to do the right thing."},{"time":315000,"text":"It is stupid that we use two tons of steel, glass and plastic"},{"time":320000,"text":"to haul our sorry selves to the shopping mall."},{"time":324000,"text":"It's stupid that we put water in plastic bottles"},{"time":327000,"text":"in Fiji and ship it here."},{"time":331000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":333000,"text":"It's hard to change consumer behavior"},{"time":335000,"text":"because consumers don't know how much this stuff costs. Do you know?"},{"time":340000,"text":"Do you know how much CO2 you generated to drive here or fly here?"},{"time":345000,"text":"I don't know, and I should."},{"time":348000,"text":"Those of us who care about all this would act better"},{"time":350000,"text":"if we knew what the real costs were."},{"time":353000,"text":"But as long as we pretend that CO2 is free,"},{"time":356000,"text":"as long as these uses are nearly invisible, how can we expect change?"},{"time":361000,"text":"I'm really afraid, because I think the kinds of changes"},{"time":365000,"text":"we can reasonably expect from individuals"},{"time":368000,"text":"are going to be clearly not enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":373000,"text":"The third lesson we learned is that policy matters. It really matters."},{"time":376000,"text":"In fact, policy is paramount."},{"time":379000,"text":"I've got a behind-the-scenes story for you"},{"time":381000,"text":"about that green tech network I described."},{"time":382000,"text":"At the end of our first meeting, we got together to talk about"},{"time":385000,"text":"what the action items would be, how we'd follow up."},{"time":389000,"text":"And Bob Epstein raised a hand. He stood up."},{"time":393000,"text":"You know, Bob's that Berkeley techie type who started Sybase."},{"time":396000,"text":"Well, Bob said the most important thing we could do right now"},{"time":400000,"text":"is to make it clear in Sacramento, California"},{"time":404000,"text":"that we need a market-based system of mandates"},{"time":407000,"text":"that's going to cap and reduce greenhouse gases in California."},{"time":412000,"text":"It's necessary and, just as important,"},{"time":415000,"text":"it's good for the California economy."}]},{"cues":[{"time":417000,"text":"So, eight of us went to Sacramento in August and we met"},{"time":420000,"text":"with the seven undecided legislators and we lobbied for AB32."},{"time":425000,"text":"You know what? Six of those seven voted yes in favor of the bill,"},{"time":428000,"text":"so it passed, and it passed by a vote of 47 to 32."},{"time":434000,"text":"(Applause)"},{"time":437000,"text":"Please. Thank you."},{"time":441000,"text":"I think it's the most important legislation of 2006. Why?"},{"time":442000,"text":"Because California was the first state in this country"},{"time":446000,"text":"to mandate 25 percent reduction of greenhouse gases by 2020."},{"time":450000,"text":"And the result of that is, we're going to generate 83,000 new jobs,"},{"time":455000,"text":"four billion dollars a year in annual income, and reduce the CO2 emissions"},{"time":459000,"text":"by 174 million tons a year."},{"time":464000,"text":"California emits only seven percent of U.S. CO2 emissions."},{"time":469000,"text":"It's only a percent and a half of the country's CO2 emissions. It's a great start,"},{"time":472000,"text":"but I've got to tell you -- where I started -- I'm really afraid."},{"time":477000,"text":"In fact, I'm certain California's not enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":481000,"text":"Here's a story about national policy that we could all learn from."},{"time":485000,"text":"You know Tom Friedman says, \"If you don't go, you don't know\"?"},{"time":488000,"text":"Well, we went to Brazil to meet Dr. Jose Goldemberg."},{"time":492000,"text":"He's the father of the ethanol revolution."},{"time":495000,"text":"He told us that Brazil's government mandated"},{"time":498000,"text":"that every gasoline station in the country would carry ethanol."},{"time":502000,"text":"And they mandated that their new vehicles"},{"time":505000,"text":"would be flex-fuel compatible, right?"},{"time":507000,"text":"They'd run ethanol or ordinary gasoline."},{"time":510000,"text":"And so, here's what's happened in Brazil."},{"time":512000,"text":"They now have 29,000 ethanol pumps --"},{"time":515000,"text":"this versus 700 in the U.S., and a paltry two in California --"},{"time":519000,"text":"and in three years their new car fleet"},{"time":521000,"text":"has gone from four percent to 85 percent flex-fuel."},{"time":526000,"text":"Compare that to the U.S.: five percent are flex-fuel."},{"time":529000,"text":"And you know what? Most consumers who have them don't even know it."},{"time":534000,"text":"So, what's happened in Brazil is, they've replaced"},{"time":537000,"text":"40 percent of the gasoline consumed by their automotive fleet with ethanol."},{"time":541000,"text":"That's 59 billion dollars since 1975"},{"time":545000,"text":"that they didn't ship to the Middle East."},{"time":547000,"text":"It's created a million jobs inside that country,"},{"time":550000,"text":"and it's saved 32 million tons of CO2. It's really substantial."},{"time":554000,"text":"That's 10 percent of the CO2 emissions across their entire country."},{"time":558000,"text":"But Brazil's only 1.3 percent of the world's CO2 emission."},{"time":562000,"text":"So, Brazil's ethanol miracle, I'm really afraid, is not enough."},{"time":569000,"text":"In fact, I'm afraid all of the best policies we have"},{"time":572000,"text":"are not going to be enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":576000,"text":"The fourth and final lesson we've learned"},{"time":578000,"text":"is about the potential of radical innovation."},{"time":580000,"text":"So, I want to tell you about a tragic problem"},{"time":582000,"text":"and a breakthrough technology."},{"time":584000,"text":"Every year a million and a half people die of"},{"time":587000,"text":"a completely preventable disease. That's malaria. 6,000 people a day."},{"time":592000,"text":"All for want of two dollars' worth of medications"},{"time":594000,"text":"that we can buy at the corner drugstore."},{"time":596000,"text":"Well, two dollars, two dollars is too much for Africa."},{"time":600000,"text":"So, a team of Berkeley researchers with 15 million dollars"},{"time":604000,"text":"from the Gates Foundation is engineering, designing a radical new way"},{"time":610000,"text":"to make the key ingredient, called artemisinin,"},{"time":614000,"text":"and they're going to make that drug 10 times cheaper."},{"time":616000,"text":"And in doing so, they'll save a million lives --"},{"time":619000,"text":"at least a million lives a year. A million lives."},{"time":622000,"text":"Their breakthrough technology is synthetic biology."},{"time":626000,"text":"This leverages millions of years of evolution"},{"time":628000,"text":"by redesigning bugs to make really useful products."},{"time":631000,"text":"Now, what you do is, you get inside the microbe,"},{"time":634000,"text":"you change its metabolic pathways, and you end up with a living chemical factory."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639000,"text":"Now, you may ask,"},{"time":641000,"text":"John, what has this got to go with green and with climate crisis?"},{"time":644000,"text":"Well, I'll tell you -- a lot."},{"time":646000,"text":"We've now formed a company called Amyris, and this technology"},{"time":650000,"text":"that they're using can be used to make better biofuels."},{"time":654000,"text":"Don't let me skip over that. Better biofuels are a really big deal."},{"time":658000,"text":"That means we can precisely engineer the molecules in the fuel chain"},{"time":662000,"text":"and optimize them along the way."},{"time":665000,"text":"So, if all goes well, they're going to have designer bugs in warm vats"},{"time":670000,"text":"that are eating and digesting sugars to excrete better biofuels."},{"time":677000,"text":"I guess that's better living through bugs."},{"time":681000,"text":"Alan Kay is famous for saying"},{"time":683000,"text":"the best way to predict the future is to invent it."},{"time":685000,"text":"And, of course, at Kleiner we, kind of, apologize and say"},{"time":688000,"text":"the second best way is to finance it."},{"time":690000,"text":"And that's why we're investing 200 million dollars"},{"time":694000,"text":"in a wide range of really disruptive new technologies"},{"time":697000,"text":"for innovation in green technologies."},{"time":699000,"text":"And we're encouraging others to do it as well."},{"time":701000,"text":"We're talking a lot about this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":703000,"text":"In 2005, there were 600 million dollars invested in new technologies"},{"time":708000,"text":"of the sort you see here. It doubled in 2006 to 1.2 billion dollars."},{"time":713000,"text":"But I'm really afraid we need much, much more."},{"time":719000,"text":"For reference, fact one:"},{"time":720000,"text":"Exxon's revenues in 2005 were a billion dollars a day."},{"time":723000,"text":"Do you know, they only invested 0.2 percent of revenues in R&amp;D?"},{"time":727000,"text":"Second fact: the President's new budget for renewable energy"},{"time":731000,"text":"is barely a billion dollars in total."},{"time":734000,"text":"Less than one day of Exxon's revenues."},{"time":737000,"text":"Third fact: I bet you didn't know that there's enough energy"},{"time":740000,"text":"in hot rocks under the country to supply America's energy needs"},{"time":745000,"text":"for the next thousand years. And the federal budget"},{"time":749000,"text":"calls for a measly 20 million dollars of R&amp;D in geothermal energy."},{"time":754000,"text":"It is almost criminal that we are not investing more"},{"time":757000,"text":"in energy research in this country."},{"time":760000,"text":"And I am really afraid that it's absolutely not enough."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765000,"text":"So, in a year's worth of learning we found a bunch of surprises."},{"time":768000,"text":"Who would have thought that a mass retailer"},{"time":770000,"text":"could make money by going green? Who would have thought that"},{"time":772000,"text":"a database entrepreneur could transform California with legislation?"},{"time":776000,"text":"Who would have thought that the ethanol biofuel miracle"},{"time":780000,"text":"would come from a developing country in South America?"},{"time":783000,"text":"And who would have thought that scientists"},{"time":785000,"text":"trying to cure malaria could come up with breakthroughs in biofuels?"},{"time":790000,"text":"And who would have thought that all that is not enough?"},{"time":795000,"text":"Not enough to stabilize the climate."},{"time":797000,"text":"Not enough to keep the ice in Greenland from crashing into the ocean."},{"time":801000,"text":"The scientists tell us -- and they're only guessing --"},{"time":803000,"text":"that we've got to reduce greenhouse gas emissions by one half,"},{"time":807000,"text":"and do it as fast as possible."},{"time":808000,"text":"Now, we may have the political will to do this in the U.S.,"},{"time":811000,"text":"but I've got to tell you, we've got only one atmosphere,"},{"time":815000,"text":"and so somehow we're going to have to find the political will"},{"time":817000,"text":"to do this all around the world. The wild card in this deck is China."}]},{"cues":[{"time":824000,"text":"To size the problem, China's CO2 emissions today are 3.3 gigatons;"},{"time":830000,"text":"the U.S. is 5.8. Business as usual means"},{"time":834000,"text":"we'll have 23 gigatons from China by 2050."},{"time":837000,"text":"That's about as much CO2 as there is in the whole world."},{"time":840000,"text":"And if it's business as usual, we're going out of business."},{"time":843000,"text":"When I was in Davos, China's Mayor of Dalian was pressed"},{"time":846000,"text":"about their CO2 strategy, and he said the following,"},{"time":849000,"text":"\"You know, Americans use seven times the CO2 per capita as Chinese.\""},{"time":854000,"text":"Then he asked, \"Why should China sacrifice our growth"},{"time":858000,"text":"so that the West can continue to be profligate and stupid?\""},{"time":862000,"text":"Does anybody here have an answer for him? I don't."},{"time":867000,"text":"We've got to make this economic so that all people and all nations"},{"time":874000,"text":"make the right outcome, the profitable outcome,"},{"time":876000,"text":"and therefore the likely outcome."},{"time":878000,"text":"Energy's a six-trillion-dollar business worldwide."},{"time":880000,"text":"It is the mother of all markets. You remember that Internet?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":884000,"text":"Well, I'll tell you what. Green technologies -- going green --"},{"time":888000,"text":"is bigger than the Internet."},{"time":889000,"text":"It could be the biggest economic opportunity of the 21st century."},{"time":893000,"text":"Moreover, if we succeed, it's going to be"},{"time":895000,"text":"the most important transformation for life on the planet since,"},{"time":899000,"text":"as Bill Joy says, we went from methane to oxygen in the atmosphere."},{"time":903000,"text":"Now, here's the hard question, if the trajectory of all the world's"},{"time":908000,"text":"companies and individuals and policies and innovation"},{"time":912000,"text":"is not going to be enough, what are we going to do? I don't know."},{"time":920000,"text":"Everyone here cares about changing the world"},{"time":923000,"text":"and has made a difference in that one way or another."}]},{"cues":[{"time":926000,"text":"So, our call to action -- my call to you --"},{"time":930000,"text":"is for you to make going green your next big thing, your gig."},{"time":937000,"text":"What can you do? You can personally get carbon neutral."},{"time":943000,"text":"Go to ClimateCrisis.org or CarbonCalculator.com"},{"time":947000,"text":"and buy carbon credits. You could join other leaders in mandating,"},{"time":952000,"text":"lobbying for mandated cap and trade in U.S. greenhouse gas reductions."},{"time":957000,"text":"There's six bills right now in Congress. Let's get one of them passed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":962000,"text":"And the most important thing you can do, I think,"},{"time":964000,"text":"is to use your personal power and your Rolodex"},{"time":966000,"text":"to lead your business, your institution, in going green."},{"time":970000,"text":"Do it like Wal-Mart, get it to go green"},{"time":972000,"text":"for its customers and its suppliers and for itself."},{"time":977000,"text":"Really think outside the box."},{"time":979000,"text":"Can you imagine what it would be like if Amazon or eBay or Google"},{"time":984000,"text":"or Microsoft or Apple really went green and you caused that to happen?"},{"time":989000,"text":"It could be bigger than Wal-Mart."},{"time":994000,"text":"I can't wait to see what we TEDsters do about this crisis."},{"time":1000000,"text":"And I really, really hope that we multiply all of our energy,"},{"time":1004000,"text":"all of our talent and all of our influence to solve this problem."},{"time":1019000,"text":"Because if we do, I can look forward"},{"time":1025000,"text":"to the conversation I'm going to have with my daughter in 20 years."},{"time":1029000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}